This is the README file for instructions on creating additionaltest cases in the LaGriT_test_suite/test_cases/ directory structure.Last Revised: 28 NOV 2000              Carl Hagelberg LANL EES-5 hagelberg@lanl.govAll directory and file creations are within the LaGriT_test_suite/test_cases/directory. To create a new test case called "newtest", first create a directory structureas follows:mkdir newtestcd newtestmkdir testcd testmkdir input_outputmkdir htmlcd htmlmkdir mkdir imagecd ..Note that the only name specific to newtest is the newtest directory itself,the directories within newtest are standardized names.cd input_output1. create the LaGriT input file named "LaGriT_input_newtest", the suffix being   specific to the new test.2. Any input files required for the LaGriT script to run should be named   as "input_*.gmv" or "input_*.inp" (.inp files are not preferred but sometimes   neccessary).3. Within the LaGriT_input_newtest file there should be a header describing   the input file, and ample comments throughout:   *TEST newtestcommand (LaGriT_input_newtest)   *   * Simple Example to ...    *   * Create a cmo with hexahedral storage arrays   cmo/create/cmo/ / / hex   *4. Any dumps should be in gmv format when possible and follow the file name   convention "output_newtest.gmv" or output_newtest1.gmv, output_newtest2.gmv,   etc. for multiple output files.5. At the end of LaGriT_input_newtest there should be a section for creating   the test suite comparison files (used by the test scripts) as follows:   * begin compare here   cmo/status   cmo/printatt//-all-/minmax   quality   finish                  6. finish should be followed by a carriage return for use on sgi's.                                    7. Any visualizations can be placed in ../html/image in *.gif format.   I've been using gmv to create rgb snapshots called image1.rgb, image2.rgb,   etc. Then I run a short script that invokes convert to create gif files,   one at usable size and one reduced to a thumbnail for use in html files:   #   convert -crop 15% image1.rgb newtest1.gif   convert -geometry 15% newtest1.gif newtest1_tn.gif   echo 'newtest1.gif and newtest1_tn.gif done\n'   #   convert -crop 15% image2.rgb newtest2.gif   convert -geometry 15% newtest2.gif newtest2_tn.gif   echo 'newtest2.gif and newtest2_tn.gif done\n'For discussion of running the test suite scripts seeLaGriT_test_suite/scripts/00README